news.title: Opposition to auction of proposed amenity plots in Pune
news.para: The Hinjewadi Employees and Residents Trust have written to the Pune Metropolitan Development Authority (PMRDA) to stop the auction process.

news.title: Property tax defaulters owe over Rs 400 crore to Nagpur civic body
news.para: For the current financial year, the NMC has set for itself a target to earn Rs 300 crore in property taxes. Till November 20, Rs 150 crore have been added to the corporation exchequer.

news.title: Chandigarh residents seek lifting of ban on share-wise sale of property
news.para: ​In its January 10 order, the Supreme Court had banned conversion of residential houses into floor-wise apartments in sectors 1-30, while stating that they carried heritage status.

news.title: Bombay HC ban on open carry of construction debris lapses, relief likely for 9,000 sites
news.para: A senior bureaucrat said the relaxation will bring relief to 9,000 construction and demolition sites, where around 1.7 lakh tonnes of debris has been lying since the high court first imposed a ban on November 6 and extended it till November 19 four days later.

news.title: Mumbai: MHADA sets policy for sale of 11,184 vacant flats across divisional boards
news.para: As per the policy specifications laid down by the authority, the divisional boards are directed to submit proposals to the government for relaxation of certain conditions for the option of ‘direct sale of apartments’ and seek approval.

news.title: NCDRC enforces Parsvnath Developers to refund, monitors timely payments
news.para: In a series of recent orders, NCDRC cracked the whip after Parsvnath Developers failed to pay refund and compensation for delay to a Delhi resident, more than three years after it directed the builder to refund the payment made by the flat buyer with interest.

news.title: Sebi board likely to discuss regulation of realty platforms, 'delisting' changes
news.para: The intention to bring in rules for investment platforms offering fractional ownership of real estate assets comes in the wake of growing demand for such products in recent times.

news.title: NCLT allows 936 days exclusion from Lok Housing's resolution process
news.para: As per the bankruptcy regulation, the lenders and the resolution professional are expected to complete the resolution process within a total of 270 days, failing which the Mumbai-based company will undergo mandatory liquidation.

news.title: Mumbai: Actor Samir Kochhar and Karishma Tanna's husband 'duped' by builder
news.para: Based on a complaint filed by Kochhar, a First Information Report was registered against Pronit Nath and his wife Amisha Nath at Andheri police station in the city under Indian Penal Code sections 120(B) (conspiracy), 409 (criminal breach of trust) and 420 (cheating), he said.

news.title: London-focused Workspace forecasts strong second-half rental growth
news.para: Flexible space operators such as Workspace have performed well on the operational front as tenants opt for short-term leases and reassess strategies periodically amid broader economic worries.

news.title: RMZ Corporation plans to double its real estate business to $40 billion by 2029
news.para: RMZ Corporation announced the appointment of Arshdeep Sethi as president of RMZ Real Estate, Thirumal Govindraj as CEO of RMZ Office, Avnish Singh as CEO of RMZ Mixed Use, Saandip Kundu as CEO of RMZ Living and Avinash Sule as CEO of RMZ Industrial & Logistics and RMZ Hospitality.

news.title: US existing home sales slump to more than 13-year low, prices accelerate
news.para: The report from the National Association of Realtors on Tuesday also showed that the median house price last month was the highest for any October.

news.title: Vietnam developers' debt deteriorates as cash falls to lowest in five years: Report
news.para: The Southeast Asian country's real estate sector has seen in recent months developers miss interest payments on debt amid a credit crunch and oversupply of high-end properties that resembles the more acute troubles in neighbouring China.

news.title: Fitch cuts Swedish SBB rating over tight liquidity, weak market
news.para: Loss-making SBB is at the centre of a Swedish property crash, having racked up vast debt by buying public real estate, including social housing, government offices, schools and hospitals.

news.title: Eight smart city projects ready for inauguration in Trichy
news.para: Among the completed projects are the multi-level car parking (MLCP) on West Boulevard Road and revamping of the fish market at Gandhi market.

news.title: Kochi to get LED streetlights, Rs 40 crore allocated for project
news.para: According to sources, CSML has allocated Rs 40 crore for the project. “The project will be started within a couple of months. The switchover to LED streetlights is expected to help us reduce our electricity bills by around 50%,” a source with the Kochi corporation said.

news.title: M3M's managing director gets anticipatory bail in money laundering case
news.para: PMLA (Prevention of Money Laundering Act) special judge Rajeev Goyal gave Bansal a blanket relief by directing the ED to give him at least a 7-day notice for arrest.

news.title: Kochi: Apple Heights residents' trying to find consensus
news.para: “We can’t collect and pay the tax dues as it will result in a huge financial burden on the flat owners. We hope to reach a consensus to use the money KMRL remitted at the court to pay off our tax dues,” said MD Varghese, joint secretary of the resident's association in a press conference on Tuesday.

news.title: Ludhiana improvement trust to start construction of stalled Atal Apartments
news.para: ​The LIT chairman said that either chief minister Bhagwant Mann or local bodies minister Balkar Singh would come for inauguration of the project at the end of this month.

news.title: HSVP kicks off survey in 18 Gurugram sectors to check commercial activities in housing units
news.para: A senior HSVP official said, “On the instructions of estate officer Suman Bhankar, the engineering wing has started the survey in sectors falling under HSVP to check if illegal commercial activities are being carried out from residential units."
